summary: Carol: Valkyrie, this is Maria, my wife, and Monica, my daughter.  Valkyrie shakes Maria’s hand. Maria: Valkyrie? Carol: Yeah,...
body:
Carol: Valkyrie, this is Maria, my wife, and Monica, my daughter.

Valkyrie shakes Maria’s hand.

Maria: Valkyrie?
Carol: Yeah, like the women warriors of Norse mythology. Except it’s not mythology. It’s all real. Thor actually introduced us.

Maria looks Valkyrie over.

Maria: She looks strong.
Carol: So are you, though, babe.

Carol kisses Maria’s cheek.
Maria: Yeah, yeah.

Valkyrie: I must say, I was expecting someone…
Maria: Closer to her age? We were about the same age once, but Carol had to go and complete her space-faring mission, and apparently because of special relativity or something, time goes faster for her when she’s flying at light speed, while it stays the same for us. So, Monica and I aged, she didn’t. Now she looks about the same age as Monica, which is, well, a trip, you know?
Valkyrie: My kind don’t age very quickly, either. If I get close to humans like you here on Midgard, I will have to deal with much the same thing as Carol.
Monica: Midgard?
Carol: It’s what Asgardians call Earth.

Maria: Right. So are you two hungry?
Valkyrie: I am not, but I could always go for a drink.
Carol: No, you couldn’t, you’re not doing that anymore, right?

Carol glares at Valkyrie pointedly.

Valkyrie: I am good, actually, thank you.
Monica: Valkyrie, we actually have some photo albums around the house, if you want to see them. My moms’ wedding pictures, my graduation.
Valkyrie: If you would like.

Valkyrie and Monica leave the room.

Maria (quietly): Why did you bring that woman into our house?
Carol: I thought you and Monica would like to meet her. She’s pretty cool, right?
Maria: How long have you known her? You’re acting married, and in case you’ve forgotten, you already have a wife.
Carol: What, that thing about her drinking? I was just being a good friend. She’s had a problem with it in the past, and I was watching out for her.
Maria: Please. I know you have a type.
Carol: Even if I did like her, I would never cheat on you.
Maria: I know, of course I know that, but…
Carol: But if you would like to fool around, just the three of us -
Maria: -Carol!
Carol: Kidding! Mostly.

Maria: I’m not going to tell you who you can or can’t spend your time with. Just be honest with me. Do you like her?
Carol: I mean, is she attractive? Yes. Would I like to take her out dancing after this stuff with Thanos is over? Also yes. Could she crush my skull with the pure force of her bare thighs alone? Absolutely. But that doesn’t mean I don’t still love you.
Maria: I know. And I also know that even if you did sleep with her, that wouldn’t make what we have just go away overnight. I’ll still love you if something happens between the two of you, and I know you’ll still love me. Just be careful, okay? Because that woman right there, she’s damaged. You can feel it.

Carol: Aren’t we all, though?
Maria: I’m serious. I don’t want to see you get hurt.

Carol wraps her arms around Maria’s waist.

Carol: I’ll be okay. Will you?
Maria: That depends. Are you staying over tonight?
Carol: Yeah, but I’ve got to be up early tomorrow to train with the Avengers.
Maria: I’ll see if I can tire you out so you get some real good sleep, baby.

Carol and Maria kiss as Valkyrie and Monica reenter the room.

Monica: Get a room, you two.
Carol: This is our house, you know.
Valkyrie: Sorry for interrupting.
Maria: It’s okay. Are you sure I can’t get you anything?
Valkyrie: No, I should go. Training tomorrow. See you then, Carol?
Carol: Yeah.

Valkyrie approaches the door out. Maria extends a hand for Valkyrie to shake once more.

Maria: It was nice meeting you, Valkyrie.

Valkyrie shakes it hardily, but avoids eye contact with Maria.

Valkyrie: You, too, Maria. It’s nice to meet the woman Carol’s been going on about. I sense that a part of you is a warrior as well, like Carol and like me.
Maria: Well, yes, I was in the air force.
Valkyrie: I can see why Carol likes you.
Maria: I can see why she likes you.

Valkyrie takes her leave.

Monica: Wow, Mom, I can’t believe you brought your girlfriend to meet Mom and me.

summary: I just saw Captain Marvel and, oh God was it good
body:
I just saw Captain Marvel and, oh God was it good

Was the best movie ever made? No. Did it have its flaws? Yes. But I can say without a doubt that I’ve never felt so empowered while watching a Marvel movie.

Don’t get me wrong. I would give Marvel my firstborn if asked and I love every movie they’ve put out, but it’s the first time I’ve seen a movie where I related so much to the protagonist.

I love Tony Stark, Steve Rogers, Thor, etc. They are literally are my baby boys, but I never saw myself in them.

Now with Carol Danvers the whole picture changes. She’s been told her whole life she couldn’t make it, that she would never be as good as a man. She was manipulated by a man who used his position as her mentor and superior to suppress her. She was told to keep her emotions in check all the time, because having feelings made her irrational and weak. And time and time and again she proved them wrong.

She embraced her flaws and her emotions and became stronger because of it. She started to listen to what she wanted instead of doing what she was told to do. She fell a thousand times and every single time she got back on her feet without anyone’s help.

Any of us could be Carol Danvers and it’s a shame that I can’t say the same about other female characters in movies or series.
